<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="peeny-butter" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Peeny Butter Fudge</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup milk</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 oz unsweetened baking chocolate</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 tablespoon butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>2 cups sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> cup creamy peanut butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon vanilla</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Combine milk, chocolate, and butter in saucepan.  Stir over low heat with wooden spoon until squares begin to melt or have melted completely.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Add sugar and stir.  Increase heat to medium and let cook until mixture is at a low boil (stirring occasionally).  Let boil for five minutes.  Test by putting drops of mixture in glass of cold water until drops look like tadpoles.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Remove from heat, and stir in vanilla.  Place saucepan in cold water until bottom is warm.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Stir in peanut butter, and beat mixture until it is not shiny.  Pour into greased 8" x 8" baking pan and let cool. Cut into ? pieces.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>